manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: The Techsol Speaker Wall Mount Brackets – Suitable for Home cinema/Satellite style speakers with Single Threaded Insert fittings

Optimum Viewing Angle The speaker wall mount brackets have a tilt & swivel to allow for optimum viewing angle and level. This means that you will be able to adjust and personalize each bracket to the angle and level you need. This also means that you do not need to spend extra time comparing different bracket angles and levels, as you can have it all with this set. This will also save you money as you will not need to purchase a new set of brackets if you wish to get a different angle or level– simply make an adjustment to your existing set!

Easy Installation The brackets are universal wall mounts for home cinema/satellite style speakers with single threaded insert fittings. You will therefore be able to enjoy your new speaker brackets within minutes, after a simple installation with the included extensive install kit. If your speaker has a single rear entry fitting with M5 metric threads (i.e. one screw threaded hole), and the speaker is under 8lbs (3.5kgs), then it will fit. They are designed to work with systems designed by companies such as: Aiwa, Akai, Audiovox, Bose, Canton, Denon, Fisher, Harmon Kardon, JVC, Kenwood, KLH, Koss, Magnavox, NHT, Oriton, Panasonic, Phillips, Pioneer, Polk Audio, RCA, Rio, Samsung, Sony, TEAC, Yamaha and more. Note: the speaker brackets DO NOT fit Logitech Z906. This product can also be used for speakers with keyhole fittings, however the fixings for these speakers are not included.

Sleek, Stylish, and Functional Speaker wall mount brackets free up space on your tv stand and floor with a sleek and modern bracket for your speakers. This means that you will have more space on your tv stand and floor for all of your home cinema needs, without sacrificing the proximity of your speakers. What's Included Included in this offer are 5 wall mount speaker brackets, as well as an installation kit (speakers not included). This means that you will not need to spend any time shopping around for the appropriate mounting hardware, as the mounting hardware you need is included. Feel Confident in Your Purchase Sold in over six countries, customers around the world give this product consistently outstanding positive feedback. This means that you can have the utmost confidence when buying the TechSol wall mounted speaker brackets for your home.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 23, 2014
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Overall great for my setup
reviews.reviewText: I bought these to use with a Polk TL1900 system so majority of this review is based with them. I did get five mounts since I read a handful only received 4. I am using deadbolt banana plugs and found these mounts to be no problem if the bananas are plugged from the side holes of the binding posts. I'm saying this because I initially had them plugged through the top as it was best for hiding the wire with my temporary setup but if you were to keep it that way with these mounts you would have to flip the mount upside down for it to fit, which does not look good at all. So for these speakers, plugged from the side, they work perfectly and they seem to be fairly well-made with good range of motion (my rears are turned against the walls with room to spare). They are also pretty small so they easily hide behind the speakers. I have mounted them with the four satellites and did not find any problem with function. They do feel solid though these speakers are not that heavy. That being said, I did have to buy a set of screws for these speaker's threaded holes, 1/4" - 20, as they do not come with the mounts as some others may have said already. They were less than $2 so it's no deal breaker. The 1/4" is just a hair to big for these mount holes but you can easily screw it in before hand to thread it in, like I did, or just drill it out a tiny tiny bit. So depending on your speaker mount hole location, such as if it was just flush with the back of the speaker, you may only need 1" length. Of coarse that's just a possibility so double check with your speakers to estimate the length. Regarding keyhole mounting, I cannot say much. My speakers are also not that big so I'm not sure about functionality and stability with bigger speakers. I will try to post some photos of them to give an idea of how they look with wire and everything. Overall they are great for my setup, I have no problems with them since I already knew about having to buy screws. I would also say they are fairly priced so I would definitely buy these again if need be.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality and gets the job done! I would buy them again.
reviews.reviewText: I have used this type of speaker monut in the past and I was pleased with them. The brand that I had bought previously was no longer in business, so I decided to give these a try. These are great speaker mounts! As you can see from my pics, my speakers are rather large, Onkyo brand speakers. I was worried after reading reviews commenting on these being cheap and flimsy, but that's not the case. I am very pleased with these speaker mounts and I would buy them again. The hardware that these come with didn't fit my speakers, but I had bolts, nuts, and washers on hand to remedy this problem. I used the keyhole to mount them and it worked perfectly. I highly recommend these!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 8, 2015
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice brackets after I made a few adjustments...
reviews.reviewText: Purchased 2 packs of these to have enough mounts for my 5.1 and 7.1 surround speaker systems. My center speakers sit on a shelf above my TV so I only needed 4 and 6 brackets for each system. The screws included to mount the speakers didn't work for my Polks so I had to purchase 1/4" - 20 x 1/2" screws to make these work. The screws did fit my Sony speakers. I also decided to drill 1/4" holes in the right or left bottom section of these brackets (se photo) so I could feed the speaker wire that was coming out of the wall through this hole, and it also allowed me to cover the hole in the wall; thus, giving a much cleaner and professional looking installation. Two of the brackets for the 7.1 system were being mounted to a white crakcle finish bead board with white Polk speakers, so I spray painted the brackets white to make them look better with the speakers and wall (see photo). After making my adjustments to these brackets they are easy to mount on the wall and hold the speakers securely no matter what angle I need to place them for proper listening. Even with having to take the time and spend a little bit of extra money to make this work for me, I am very happy with these brackets and would buy them again. The price was great and the quality is well worth it.

reviews.reviewTitle: Reliable mounts with a slightly tricky installation process
reviews.reviewText: The product itself is really good. The Adjustable speaker mounts that work great with my Bose Acoustimass satellite speakers. Installation was a bit tricky single handedly since you need to hold onto the speaker while trying to align and screw it into the wall mount. Perhaps a butterfly screw would have been a better option here. There are adequate screws provided to fix the brackets to the wall (including wall plugs) and screws to attach the speaker to the bracket as well. A couple of the wall mounting screws were faulty (the Philips head groove was covered due to manufacturing defects). We just used our own screws to complete the job. All in all a really good product.
Product does just as it says. I use them for my bose 5.1 speakers and they work perfectly fine. Great.
